 <b>Gervaise</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705183,"age":6,"year":"1086","julianDay":2117714,"title":"Domesday Book","description":"Domesday Book is Britain's earliest extant public record with information containing land surveys and landholdings commissioned by William I. The book was completed in 1086.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/domesday/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Domesday","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705184,"age":16,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705185,"age":26,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Gervase de Throckmorton III was born in 1080, in Throckmorton, Worcestershire, England, his father, Gervase de Throckmorton II, was 38 and his mother, Mrs Gervase De THROCKMORTON II, was 38. He had at least 2 sons with Mrs Gervais de Throckmorton III. He died in 1135, in his hometown, at the age of 55, and was buried in Throckmorton, Worcestershire, England."},"et":{"1080–1135":"1080–1135","1080–Female":"1080–Surnud","1110–1154":"1110–1154","1112–Male":"1112–Surnud","1042–Male":"1042–Surnud","1042–Female":"1042–Surnud","1080":"1080","1106":"1106","1135":"1135","1112":"1112","1154":"1154","1110":"1110","about 1112":"umbes 1112","1086":"1086","1042":"1042","1096":"1096","about 1110":"umbes 1110","Throckmorton, Worcestershire, England":"Throckmorton, Worcestershire, England"},"fi":{"1080–1135":"1080–1135","1080–Female":"1080–Kuollut","1110–1154